observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:
a. Require the Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of local road networks and ensure that the report is provided with detailed breakdown and cost segregation of each road component;
b. Thereafter, instruct the Mun. Accountant, in coordination with the Mun. Engineer and the OIC-GSO, to reconcile the RPCLRN with the appropriate records and prepare the journal voucher to update the Road Networks account in the books of accounts;
c. Enjoin the Mun. Accountant and the Acting GSO to maintain complete and updated Local Road Network Ledger Cards (LRNLCs) and Local Road Network Property Cards (LRNPCs), respectively, in accordance with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and
d. Ensure that the physical count of local road networks is undertaken annually, and the reports thereon are submitted to the Audit Team and the Mun. Accountant not later than January 31 of each year.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the Municipal Engineer, Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator and Municipal General Services Officer to:
comply with the required posting of information and publicity of government programs/projects/activities in the municipal premises and at the projects’ sites;
provide the Audit Team with the list of government PPAs to be implemented for a particular year at the beginning of the year with the complete information such as: project name; implementing unit; office or division if it is not the agency as a whole; brief description of the PPAs; contractor or supplier, if any; mode of procurement; funding source; cost or approved budget; project duration including start and completion dates; and location;
inform the Audit Team within ten days after the award of the projects or before the start of the programs/projects/activities that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted at the agency premises and at the project sites; and
submit monthly monitoring report on the implementation of all Municipality’s PPAs  in accordance to COA Circular No. 2013-004.
